channel.title: Does anyone have an unmodified 317 item.cfg?
channel.description:
Serious post by the way. I'm looking for that item.cfg file that comes with a ton of older server bases, but all the ones that I looked at are modified and they have the bonuses or alch values fucked up or have displaced and overwritten item IDs. Would really appreciate it if you could post or upload one for me.
Thanks.

item.title: Does anyone have an unmodified 317 item.cfg?
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“Whackatre, post:3, topic:553997”][quote author=sk8rdude461 link=topic=672919.msg4499892#msg4499892 date=1449103544]
Is this it by chance?
Click me
I found it in cheezscape.

I may have a different one if that’s not what you’re looking for.
[/quote]

thanks, looks good dude, but is there a formula to get the actual high alch prices from this list? iirc the three values that precede the bonuses are shop value, low alch and then high alch. but if you compare these numbers with the actual high alch costs, they’re different.

like a fire battlestaff is supposed to alch for 9300, but the number it shows is 12981.34.[/quote]
I’m not sure tbh.
In PI’s I typically see high alch value done like:

Which, as you can guess… it’s not even using the high alch value.

And then in cheezscape specifically, this is how they handle it:

int alchvaluez = (int)Math.floor(GetItemShopValue(castOnItem, 0, castOnSlot));
alchvaluez = (alchvaluez / 3);
addItem(995, alchvaluez);

which again, ignores the actual alch value.
